* The oldest and most direct coast-to-coast airway,
United Air Lines' "Main Line is arrow-straight from
New York, Philadelphia, Cleveland, Chicago and other
principal Eastern and Great Lakes cities to principal
points on the Pacific Coast.
Over it United flies swift, convenient overnight
schedules in the new Mainliner Sleepers as well as
scenic daylight flights in the deluxe Skylounge Main-
liners. In addition, Douglas and Boeing three-mile-a-
minute planes provide frequent inter-city service and
link intermediate points with terminals for connections
with through schedules.
United's 'Main Line" service is operated with clock-
like efficiency, its fleet of airliners backed by 1,000
skilled technicians, and other ground personnel. Dis-
tinctive, too, is United's famous personalized passenger
service with highest standards of comfort and hospitality.
Fly United's Main Line - from the East to "Every.
where West."
